In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation recognizing National Volunteer Week. He acknowledges the contributions of Americans who generously give their time and talents to help improve the lives of others. He emphasizes the importance of volunteerism in building a better future and highlights the historical significance of volunteers in the nation's success and prosperity. The article mentions that in 2017, the number of Americans volunteering reached a record high, with their contributions estimated to be worth $167 billion in economic value. The president also pays tribute to the servant leadership of those who volunteered to help fellow citizens after natural disasters, and encourages all Americans to observe National Volunteer Week by participating in service projects and making service a part of their daily lives.